"&#xa0;\nWritten \nevidence submitted by Regain Polymers Limited\n&#xa0;\nExecutive summary:&#xa0;In my capacity as both Purchasing Director of Regain Polymers Limited and Vice Chair of the British Plastics Federation Recycling Group, I make the following written submission to the Environmental Audit Committee’s inquiry on Plastic Bags.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Background:&#xa0;&#xa0;\nDangers of Biodegradable Plastic: &#xa0;\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nDrainage piping\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nDrainage chambers\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nDamp Proof Membrane\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nWheel Bins\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nCoat hangers\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nStorage boxes\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nPallets\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nGround stabilisation grids\nAll these articles are expected to be long term durable and retain their structural integrity.              Degradable content would therefore be highly inappropriate and would almost certainly result in product failure over the short rather than long term.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRecommendations: &#xa0;\nBernard Chase25 November 2013\n&#xa0;\n"